        <Base:Descriptions>
          <Base:Description type="brief">
             octopus' carcass
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="examine">
             The fresh corpse of the great octopus sprawls lifelessly. Eight beaten, cut and bruised arms with suction cups on the undersides look like they might be good trophies if you <acmd tag="command" cmd="sever tentacle">sever</acmd> them from the carcass. Most of the mass is a uniquely wounded head. The bulbous head sports two glazed over black eyes and a breakable beak.
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="look">
             The dead body of the great octopus.
          </Base:Description>
        </Base:Descriptions>
